"Zuma must fall" chanted a group of people as Zuma was starting his speech. The chanting forced Zuma to pause for few seconds. The group was later removed from the giant tents erected at the sports ground in Tshing in Ventersdorp. Zuma had earlier arrived to a rousing welcome as the crowd stood and waved as he walked into the tent, flanked by Arts and Culture Minister Nathi Mthethwa and North West premier Supra Mahumapelo.  To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
